releases/0/tender/title: Suppy of Spares in Support of Improved Tented Camps
releases/0/tender/description:
Improved Tented Camps. Babcock DSG acting on behalf of the Authority has under consideration the award of a 2 year Framework Agreement with a 1 year option year for the supply of spares in support of Improved Tented Camps,all codified  to various DMC's.

All items in scope of the requirement are codified to NATO Stock Numbers and defined by manufacturers part numbers. Babcock DSG reserves the right to add further items of similar nature post contract award.

Any resulting Framework Agreement shall contain a set of Key Performance Indicators to measure performance areas such as; delivery and quality, and shall include remedies for poor performance.

A electronic copy of the draft tender documentation are provided at Part 2 of the DPPQ link provided in this Notice. These documents are offered for information only and you are not required to comment/ respond to them. You should only submit a response to the DPPQ.

Additional information: To view this notice, register as a supplier here:

http://www.contracts.mod.uk/delta/signup.html?userType=supplier

and search for the notice with reference 'UK-Telford: Sanitary ware.'.

releases/0/tender/description:
This Contract covers the inspection and testing of all electrical installations, belonging to Southend Borough Council that are managed by South Essex Homes. (South Essex Homes is an Arms Length Management Organisation owned by Southend Borough Council) The electrical testing shall be carried out in accordance with IEE Wiring Regulations Seventeenth Edition BS 7671:2008 Requirements for Electrical Installations including amendments 1, 2 and 3 plus any amendments or Editions that may be added between April 1st 2016 & March 31st 2021. IEE Guidance Note 3, Inspection & Testing shall be used for verification of testing procedures. 

This Contract does not cover works to private or leasehold properties and payment shall only be made for works to Council buildings under the control of South Essex Homes. In addition to testing and inspecting the Contractor shall record all results and also carry out any minor repairs as per the Schedule for Variations.
